205 SPAM2~

Syntax: spam2 <options> <message>

This is a new command that lets you broadcast a message in different
fonts.  'spam2 <message>' by itself will use the default font.  If you would
like to use a different font, type 'spam2 -f <font name> message'.  You can
choose from the fonts listed in 'help spamfonts'.  There are also two other
options: you can make the message broadcast to the entire MUD, or just to
you (without any options, spam2 sends message to room).  You do this by
using '-g' (global) or '-m' (me).  
 
Ex: 'spam2 hello'.................sends Hello to room in normal font
Ex: 'spam2 -f banner hello'.......sends Hello to room in 'banner' font
Ex: 'spam2 -gf 3-d hello'.........sends Hello to entire MUD in '3-d' font
Ex: 'spam2 -m hello'..............sends Hello to you only, in normal font
 
Note: If the -f option is used, the next word must be a font name.
~

-1 ROLEPLAY RPS~
If you ended up here, you likely know what RP (Role-playing) is.  Just in
case you don't, the simplest way of putting it is using your imagination.
When you roleplay, you pretend you are a character other than yourself and
speak and act as that character. Two terms you should be familiar with are
IC (In Character) and OOC (Out Of Character).  Anything marked IC applies
to the RP context of the game.  Anything OOC refers to the players or the
game mechanics outside of roleplay.  Please use these two communication
types appropriately. Distortions of Chaos encourages and rewards, but does 
not enforce, roleplay.  Roleplay Points (RPs) can be used to benefit your
character in various ways.  A list of rewards has not be determined yet. 

All the gods and clans have help files if you would like more information
on their RP.  To set your RP flag and speak IC, type RP.  To speak OOC
by default again, type RP again.  This is a togglable flag.

See also {YHELP STORY{x and {YHELP SPEND{x.
~

-1 STORY~
Everything begins with nothing, the endless empty void.  This world was no
different.  At its beginning, when the nothing first became something, the
darkness came first, then the light for contrast.  Thus the world was born
of shadows, the blending of light and darkness, built in the crux of both.
The hands of the great god Distortions sculpted the shadows into the earth
and hung it between light and darkness, between what we now know as heaven
and hell.  Pleased with his work, he gave it life, sending all of creation
into motion with a single spark of chaos.

Chaos is what brought us to life and what keeps us alive.  Without it, all
would stagnate and die, the cycle would end and the shadows dissipate.  It
is what the gods seek, what starts their wars; they all wish to hold power
over chaos, the one uncontrollable force.

Who wields this untamed power now?  Is it Khaos, Emissary of the Void come
to sow despair and destruction?  Is it Shartyn, Frozen Temptress spreading
lies and misinformation? Perhaps it is King Garm, maintaining the illusion
of control while his own motives go unseen?  Or is it Distortions, the god
of gods, creator of this world, who hovers beyond the shadows, pulling all
our strings?
~

-1 Heaven~
Heaven is as much an idea as a physical location.  It is said by the wisest
sages that all who walk in light are within the realm of Heaven.   However,
Heaven does exist as a physical plane separating life and death.  It is the
polar opposite of Hell, which also serves as an intermediary between breath
and oblivion.  The denizens of Heaven are called Eladrin, their large wings
and unearthly beauty setting them apart from humans.  No one god holds rule
over Heaven.  The Eladrin have their own society and govern themselves with
their own laws and morality. For as long as their history has been recorded
the Eladrin have been at war with the Demons,  the vile beings who populate
Hell.
~

-1 Hell~
It is thought that those who walk in darkness are within the realm of Hell,
and this is as much true as those who believe Hell a tangible plane of vile
torment.  Heaven and Hell are forever linked, eternally engaged in a war of
light and darkness, forever separating life from death.  No god holds reign
over Hell, though many may make claim.  Several devils and demon lords have
laid claim to various regions of hell and have demons, the vile beings that
live in hell, who serve them. Some say it is Khaos who keeps rule over hell
and its demons, but this is untrue.  The Followers of the Void led by Khaos
reside among the Five Rivers of Hell, the boundaries between life and death
where they can be closer to the Void, the plane of oblivion.
~

