History:
Little is known of Shartyn's distant past, or her recent absence and consequential fall from
power.  Prior to her fall, she was a quite powerful goddess, with many followers.  She embraces
knowledge and the power that possessing it holds over others.  Having ultimate control was an
ever-present goal.  Constantly "in the know," little escaped her ever-watching eyes.  She had
endless power over ice, snow, and other cold things, controlling them as she pleased.  Without
Shartyn around to guard her own portfolio, Jade stole trickery and illusion on her own rise.
Having fallen from power, Shartyn currently wanders the realms in the form of an icling, keeping
mostly to herself, perhaps biding her time?
~

-1 Sages Twilight Grove~
{DS{ma{wg{me{Ds {xof {mT{Dw{wi{Wli{wg{Dh{mt {gG{Gr{yo{rv{ge{x

For ages scholars and adventurers alike have sought the Twilight Grove
for within this strange forest flows the Spring of Knowledge, reported
to rejuvenate the minds of all who partake of its clear water.  Within
this small forest it is always autumn,  the leaves of the trees caught
in constant change.  The time is always twilight,  the sky perpetually
the shady violet of dusk.  This is a place of transition and growth, a
locus of learning.

Recent times have seen a strange settling at the Grove as students and
sages of all sorts have decided to remain near the spring and study in
this place of abundant thought.  Modest homes and grand libraries have
sprung up among the oak and hazel woods.  Though these settlers are of
a broad variety of backgrounds and ethnicities,  though their areas of
expertise are as varied as the everchanging hues around them, they are
all of like-mind in their quests for knowledge.  Most appreciate their
new-found home and the company of others with intellectual pursuits. A
collective has been formed from these sage men and women, both to keep
safe the grove they hold sacred and to contribute to the documentation
of knowledge.  They spend their time philosophizing and writing, their
shared ideas kept in manuscripts available to all who seek to learn.

Currently, the collective is lead by a council of those most dedicated
to the cause of educating the realms.  They welcome with open arms any
who wish to help them in their noble efforts.

