Those attracted to the void are an ecclectic group.  Some are drawn to the
complete lack of morality and utter depravity associated with nothingness.
Some feel a connection with the emptiness and oblivion,  at peace with the
inevitable unimportance and impermanence of everything. Then there are the
ones filled with the desire to bring about the annihilation of everything,
to aid the void in its manifestation.

Khaos is a personification of the void, a small sliver of nothingness come
to answer the call of the void's followers, to give guidance to their work
and cause. When it manifests physically, it is a distortion in reality, an
emptiness that has no true form.  Since its induction into this world, its
hunger has been insatiable. Constantly empty, it seeks to consume anything
that crosses its path.  Therefore, to cross Khaos would mean certain death
and oblivion.

The tenets of the  Nihilists are few as the  Followers of the Void believe
in nothing save the inevitability of oblivion.  They care not for good nor
evil and tend toward chaotic behaviors.  Though conflict amongst followers
is not unheard of and rarely goes punished, one rule all live by and shall
be judged by is that  should any fellow Nihilist call for aid in welcoming
a foe into the dark oblivion, the call must be answered.  Failure to do so
may result in severe punishment requiring a sacrifice to Khaos, a pennance
for negligence to the only truth.

