                       DR mob guidelines.
**********************************************************************
The reason for this help is to keep the mud in constant balance as not
to cause major screw ups later on.  So instead of spending countless
hours over-going what should have been done correctly the first time.
You are to follow these guidelines. 

-For mobs with the shield sanctuary you want to lower it's hitdice by 
40%. (see: adjusted mob stats)
-For mobs that have any "spec fun" that is offensive lower it's 
hitdice by 25%. This means if you give a mob spec_mage you need to 
lower the damdice by 25%, if a mob has spec_thief you don't need to 
make this adjustment. (see: adjusted mob stats)
-For mobs with the shield ice/fire/shockshield you need to lower it's 
hitdice by 25%. Do not lower it's hitdice by 75% if you give it all 
three shields, and only lower it's hitdice by 25% if it has all three, 
not if it only has one. (see: adjusted mob stats)
-For a mob that has a weapon wielded lower it's damdice by 25%.(see: 
adjusted mob stats)

                   Guidelines for eq/weapon mobs.
**********************************************************************
When making a mob and you decide to give it good equipment or a good 
weapon you must make the mob harder to defeat. If you give a mob a 
good weapon you need to lower it's damdice by 25%, but also you need 
to make the mob harder to defeat. Well there are a few ways to do 
this, 
first by adding some resistances and some immunities, good ones to use 
here are the more "popular" types of damage. Like pierce and slash, 
acid, fire and ice. Try and use resistances more than immunities 
because giving a mob more than 2 or 3 immunities makes them very hard. 
You can also give the mob a bigger variety of offensive skills and or 
"spec fun" as well as some shields and affects. What we are trying to 
do here is make it difficult for players to get "good" eq and or a 
weapon. So if you have a good level 50 weapon on a mob, it should be 
an extremely hard fight for a lvl 50 player, they should have a chance 
of death. If the eq or weapon a mob has is really not that good you 
don't need to make the mob very difficult.



                   Guidelines for leveling mobs.
**********************************************************************
This is really easy to do, but you want to watch your self and not 
make them to easy. Basically you want to make leveling mobs easier to 
defeat than mobs with eq and weapons. To do this you can not give it 
very many shields, few offensive skills, no "spec-fun" and few 
res/imm, but give it more vulnerabilities. The basic off skills a mob 
has to have is dodge, parry, fast, trip, fade, and added affect haste. 
This is only if you don't want to give it any other off skills or any 
"spec fun."

